&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Junior would undoubtedly chooseÂ the &lt;a title=&#34;Botanical Garden, Padua&#34; href=&#34;http://www.ortobotanico.unipd.it/en/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Botanical Garden&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From delicate flowering plants to fascinating carnivorous ones, the Botanical Garden of Padua is home to a vast collection. Here, we spottedÂ the alpine Himalayan Cedar, peeredÂ (not too closely)Â at the poisonous plantsÂ andÂ examined the rare species. Take a break at the Fountain of the Four Seasons,Â enjoy aÂ walk up the little hillock in the garden, marvel at nature.&lt;/p&gt;

